(1) Subject to regulation 7, an agency worker (A) shall be entitled to the same basic working and employment conditions as A would be entitled to for doing the same job had A been recruited by the hirer—
(a) other than by using the services of a temporary work agency; and
(b) at the time the qualifying period commenced.

(2) For the purposes of paragraph (1), the basic working and employment conditions are—
(a) where A would have been recruited as an employee or worker, the relevant terms and conditions that are ordinarily included in the contracts of employees or workers (as the case may be) of the hirer;
(b) where there are no such employees or workers, the relevant terms and conditions that would have applied had A been recruited by the hirer other than through a temporary work agency.

(4) For the purposes of paragraph (2), the relevant terms and conditions are terms and conditions relating to—
(a) pay;
(b) the duration of working time;
(c) night work;
(d) rest periods;
(e) rest breaks; and
(f) annual leave.

(1) This regulation applies where—
(a) an agency worker has completed two or more assignments with a hirer (H) (whether or not those assignments were for the same role with H or the same temporary work agency); or
(b) an agency worker has completed at least one assignment with H and at least one assignment with a hirer connected to H.

(2) Regulation 7(2) does not apply to an agency worker who is a complainant in proceedings under these Regulations if the employment tribunal determines that it is likely that the structure of the assignment, or the assignments, was such that the most likely explanation for that structure was that H, or the temporary work agency supplying the agency worker to H, or H acting together with one or more temporary work agencies, intended to prevent the agency worker from being entitled to, or from continuing to be entitled to, the rights conferred by regulation 5.

(4) In making a determination under paragraph (2), the employment tribunal must have regard to—
(a) the length of each assignment that the agency worker has carried out with H or a connected hirer;
(b) the number of assignments that the agency worker has carried out with H or a connected hirer;
(c) the number of roles that the agency worker has worked in with H or a connected hirer;
(d) the number of times the agency worker has returned to work with H or a connected hirer in the same role following a break; and
(e) the period of any break between assignments with H or a connected hirer.
